# Console Rules (Condensed)

- Canonical source: `AGENTS.md`.
- Project identity: Console is a local AI coding control plane.
- Scope now: workspace/repo/worker selection, chat-triggered runs, streaming output.
- Keep control plane (state/routing/API) separate from execution plane (worker adapters).
- Use explicit adapters for Cursor CLI, Claude CLI, and Codex CLI.
- Do not hard-code one worker implementation into core business logic.
- Prefer simple, local-first solutions; avoid premature distributed orchestration, queue systems, and heavy infra.
- Storage default: file-based config/state under `~/.console/`; defer SQLite until justified by history/indexing/query needs.
- Repos are external filesystem source-of-truth; `~/.console/workspaces/` is Console-owned metadata/cache/artifacts.
- Default stack: backend Go, frontend Vite + React + Tailwind.
- Default streaming transport: SSE unless a strong reason exists.
- Keep modules small and composable; favor clarity over abstraction-heavy frameworks.
- Update docs in `docs/` when behavior or architecture changes.
- Document architectural decisions when introduced.
